{
  "local_port": 33210,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some yummy vegetarian recipes?",
  "response": "Here are some delicious vegetarian recipes that are full of flavor and easy to prepare:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Vegetable Stir-Fry with Tamari-Ginger Sauce**\n   - **Ingredients**: Broccoli, bell peppers, carrots, snap peas, tofu (or tempeh), garlic, ginger, tamari (or soy sauce), sesame oil, rice vinegar, and sesame seeds.\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Saut\u00e9 minced garlic and ginger in sesame oil.\n     2. Add chopped vegetables and tofu, stir-frying until tender.\n     3. Mix tamari, rice vinegar, and a bit of maple syrup for sweetness. Pour over the stir-fry.\n     4. Serve over rice or noodles, garnished with sesame seeds.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Spinach and Ricotta Stuffed Shells**\n   - **Ingredients**: Jumbo pasta shells, ricotta cheese, spinach, garlic, Parmesan cheese, marinara sauce, and mozzarella cheese.\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Cook pasta shells and set aside.\n     2. Mix ricotta, saut\u00e9ed spinach, garlic, and Parmesan in a bowl.\n     3. Stuff the shells with the mixture and place them in a baking dish.\n     4. Pour marinara sauce over the shells and sprinkle with mozzarella.\n     5. Bake at 375\u00b0F (190\u00b0C) for 20\u201325 minutes until bubbly.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Vegetarian Buddha Bowl**\n   - **Ingredients**: Quinoa (or rice), roasted sweet potatoes, chickpeas, avocado, kale, cucumber, tahini dressing.\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Cook quinoa and roast sweet potatoes with olive oil, salt, and paprika.\n     2. Assemble the bowl with quinoa, roasted sweet potatoes, chickpeas, sliced avocado, and chopped kale.\n     3. Drizzle with tahini dressing (mix tahini, lemon juice, garlic, and water).\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Caprese Stuffed Avocados**\n   - **Ingredients**: Avocados, cherry tomatoes, fresh mozzarella, basil, balsamic glaze, olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Halve avocados and remove the pit.\n     2. Fill with cherry tomatoes, mozzarella balls, and fresh basil leaves.\n     3. Drizzle with balsamic glaze and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Vegetarian Lentil Tacos**\n   - **Ingredients**: Lentils, taco seasoning, tortillas, lettuce, tomatoes, avocado, salsa, and shredded cheese (optional).\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Cook lentils and mix with taco seasoning.\n     2. Warm tortillas and fill with lentils, lettuce, tomatoes, avocado, and salsa.\n     3. Add cheese if desired.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Butternut Squash Risotto**\n   - **Ingredients**: Arborio rice, butternut squash, vegetable broth, onion, garlic, Parmesan cheese, sage, and olive oil.\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Saut\u00e9 onion and garlic in olive oil, then add Arborio rice and toast briefly.\n     2. Gradually add vegetable broth, stirring until the rice is creamy.\n     3. Add roasted butternut squash, sage, and Parmesan cheese. Stir to combine.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Vegetable Paella**\n   - **Ingredients**: Arborio or paella rice, saffron, bell peppers, artichoke hearts, peas, tomatoes, garlic, onion, and smoked paprika.\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Saut\u00e9 onion, garlic, and bell peppers in olive oil.\n     2. Add rice, smoked paprika, and saffron, stirring to coat.\n     3. Add diced tomatoes and vegetable broth, cooking until the rice is tender.\n     4. Add peas and artichoke hearts, cooking until heated through.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Chickpea Curry (Chana Masala)**\n   - **Ingredients**: Chickpeas, tomatoes, onion, garlic, ginger, garam masala, turmeric, cumin, coriander, and coconut milk.\n   - **Instructions**:\n     1. Saut\u00e9 onion, garlic, and ginger in oil.\n     2. Add spices and cook until fragrant.\n     3. Add diced tomatoes and chickpeas, simmering for 10\u201315 minutes.\n     4. Stir in coconut milk for creaminess. Serve with rice or naan.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you'd like more detailed instructions or additional recipe ideas! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
